      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction; Jan 23 article about new DVDs referred incorrectly to title of one movie</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Critic's Choice column on Tuesday, about new DVDs, referred imprecisely to the title of Sergio Leone's pioneering spaghetti western, which was modeled on Akira Kurosawa's ''Yojimbo.'' The Leone movie was released in the United States as ''A Fistful of Dollars'' and is known by that title -- not by ''For a Fistful of Dollars,'' which is a translation of the Italian title.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Critic's Choice column on Tuesday, about new DVDs, referred imprecisely to the title of Sergio Leone's pioneering spaghetti western, which was modeled on Akira Kurosawa's ''Yojimbo.'' The Leone movie was released in the United States as ''A Fistful of Dollars'' and is known by that title -- not by ''For a Fistful of Dollars,'' which is a translation of the Italian title.</p>
      </block>
